    "what_description": "Helichrysum \u00d7 ambiguum is a hybrid species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae. It is a perennial plant that grows up to 1 meter in height, with a woody base and an erect stem, bearing narrow, lance-shaped leaves that are 2-5 centimeters in length. The plant produces clusters of small, yellow or white flowers at the end of its stem, each flower consisting of five petals and numerous tiny florets. The flowers are arranged in a capitulum, a type of inflorescence typical of the Asteraceae family. The plant is native to South Africa and has been cultivated for its ornamental value and for use in traditional medicine.",
