    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Helichrysum \u00d7 ambiguum are derived from its flowers and leaves, which contain sesquiterpene lactones, flavonoids, and volatile oils. Helichrysum \u00d7 ambiguum tincture is prepared by macerating its flowers in a solvent, typically ethanol or glycerin, to create a concentrated liquid extract used to treat wounds, reduce inflammation, and alleviate pain. Essential oil of Helichrysum \u00d7 ambiguum is obtained through steam distillation of its flowers, which is used topically to reduce inflammation, improve skin health, and relieve anxiety. Helichrysum \u00d7 ambiguum salve is a topical cream or ointment prepared by infusing its flowers in a carrier oil, often combined with beeswax, to create a protective barrier for wounds and skin irritations. Additionally, tea and infused oil preparations of Helichrysum \u00d7 ambiguum are used to promote relaxation, reduce stress, and alleviate digestive issues due to its bioactive compounds.",
